cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.CV 

The paper introduces a new structural design for improving recurrent neural networks (RNNs) and evaluates its performance on several tasks using different RNN models. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Among these, cs.LG and cs.NE are the most likely categories, as they are directly related to the topic of machine learning and neural networks. However, cs.CL, cs.AI, and cs.CV are also possible categories, as they are closely related to natural language processing, artificial intelligence, and computer vision, respectively, which are all areas where RNNs are commonly used.
